{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YHKAJzmAiRCzbuVeoADmj2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Story 3.3: Onboard Alias\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆStatus: verifying\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆ<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6ŌåÆ\n     7ŌåÆ## Story\n     8ŌåÆ\n     9ŌåÆAs an operator,\n    10ŌåÆI want `codeharness onboard` to work the same as `codeharness audit`,\n    11ŌåÆso that existing scripts and docs don't break when the audit command replaces onboard.\n    12ŌåÆ\n    13ŌåÆ## Acceptance Criteria\n    14ŌåÆ\n    15ŌåÆ1. **Given** `codeharness onboard` is run with no subcommand and no flags, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical output to `codeharness audit` (same dimension checks, same status/metric format, same exit code). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16ŌåÆ2. **Given** `codeharness onboard --fix` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical output and behavior to `codeharness audit --fix` (generates fix stories for gaps, updates sprint state). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17ŌåÆ3. **Given** `codeharness onboard --json` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical JSON output to `codeharness audit --json` (same structure, same fields). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18ŌåÆ4. **Given** `codeharness onboard --fix --json` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical output to `codeharness audit --fix --json` (includes `fixStories` array in JSON). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19ŌåÆ5. **Given** the harness is not initialized, **When** `codeharness onboard` is run, **Then** it exits with `[FAIL] Harness not initialized -- run codeharness init first` and exit code 1 ŌĆö same as `codeharness audit`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20ŌåÆ6. **Given** `codeharness onboard scan` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it prints a deprecation warning `[WARN] 'onboard scan' is deprecated ŌĆö use 'codeharness audit' instead` and then runs the audit command (maps legacy subcommand to new behavior). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21ŌåÆ7. **Given** the old `registerOnboardCommand` function, **When** the alias is implemented, **Then** the old onboard command registration is removed from `src/index.ts` and replaced by the alias registration, so there is no duplicate command registration. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22ŌåÆ8. **Given** `codeharness --help` is run, **When** the help output is displayed, **Then** both `audit` and `onboard` appear in the command list, with `onboard` described as `Alias for audit ŌĆö check all compliance dimensions`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23ŌåÆ\n    24ŌåÆ## Tasks / Subtasks\n    25ŌåÆ\n    26ŌåÆ- [x] Task 1: Rewrite `src/commands/onboard.ts` as a thin alias (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8)\n    27ŌåÆ  - [x] 1.1: Remove all existing scan/coverage/audit/epic subcommand logic, shared state, and formatting helpers from `src/commands/onboard.ts`\n    28ŌåÆ  - [x] 1.2: Implement `registerOnboardCommand(program)` that creates a `program.command('onboard')` with description `'Alias for audit ŌĆö check all compliance dimensions'`\n    29ŌåÆ  - [x] 1.3: Mirror the `--json` and `--fix` options from the audit command\n    30ŌåÆ  - [x] 1.4: In the action handler, delegate directly to the same logic as `registerAuditCommand` by calling the audit action internals (either extract shared handler or import and call `runAudit` / `generateFixStories` / `addFixStoriesToState` / formatting directly)\n    31ŌåÆ  - [x] 1.5: Add deprecated `scan` subcommand that prints `[WARN] 'onboard scan' is deprecated ŌĆö use 'codeharness audit' instead` then runs audit logic (AC #6)\n    32ŌåÆ\n    33ŌåÆ- [x] Task 2: Extract shared audit action handler (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5)\n    34ŌåÆ  - [x] 2.1: Extract the audit action logic from `src/commands/audit.ts` into a shared function `executeAudit(opts: { isJson: boolean; isFix: boolean }): Promise<void>` in a new file `src/commands/audit-action.ts` (or keep inline if both commands can import the same handler)\n    35ŌåÆ  - [x] 2.2: Have both `registerAuditCommand` and `registerOnboardCommand` use the same handler, ensuring identical behavior\n    36ŌåÆ  - [x] 2.3: Keep `registerAuditCommand` in `src/commands/audit.ts` unchanged (or with minimal refactor to use extracted handler)\n    37ŌåÆ\n    38ŌåÆ- [x] Task 3: Update `src/index.ts` registration (AC: #7)\n    39ŌåÆ  - [x] 3.1: Verify `registerOnboardCommand(program)` is still called in `src/index.ts` ŌĆö the function name stays the same, only the implementation changes\n    40ŌåÆ  - [x] 3.2: Verify no duplicate `audit` or `onboard` commands are registered\n    41ŌåÆ\n    42ŌåÆ- [x] Task 4: Remove dead code (AC: #7)\n    43ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.1: Remove imports for `scanCodebase`, `analyzeCoverageGaps`, `auditDocumentation` from `src/lib/scanner.js` if no longer used elsewhere\n    44ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.2: Remove imports for `generateOnboardingEpic`, `writeOnboardingEpic`, `formatEpicSummary`, `promptApproval`, `importOnboardingEpic` from `src/lib/epic-generator.js` if no longer used elsewhere\n    45ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.3: Remove imports for `listIssues`, `createIssue` from `src/lib/beads.js` (onboard no longer calls beads directly)\n    46ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.4: Remove imports for `filterTrackedGaps`, `findVerificationGaps`, `findPerFileCoverageGaps`, `findObservabilityGaps`, `getOnboardingProgress` from `src/lib/onboard-checks.js` if no longer used\n    47ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.5: Remove imports for `saveScanCache`, `loadValidCache` from `src/lib/scan-cache.js` if no longer used\n    48ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.6: Remove imports for `appendOnboardingEpicToSprint` from `src/lib/beads-sync.js` if no longer used\n    49ŌåÆ  - [x] 4.7: Check all removed imports ŌĆö do NOT delete the library files themselves, only remove the imports from `onboard.ts`. Other commands may still use them.\n    50ŌåÆ\n    51ŌåÆ- [x] Task 5: Update tests (AC: all)\n    52ŌåÆ  - [x] 5.1: Rewrite `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` to test the alias behavior:\n    53ŌåÆ    - Test `codeharness onboard` delegates to audit logic\n    54ŌåÆ    - Test `codeharness onboard --fix` delegates to audit --fix logic\n    55ŌåÆ    - Test `codeharness onboard --json` produces same output as audit --json\n    56ŌåÆ    - Test `codeharness onboard scan` prints deprecation warning and runs audit\n    57ŌåÆ    - Test precondition failure (harness not initialized) produces same error as audit\n    58ŌåÆ  - [x] 5.2: Mock the same dependencies as `audit.test.ts` (runPreconditions, runAudit, formatAuditHuman, formatAuditJson, generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState)\n    59ŌåÆ  - [x] 5.3: Verify the `--help` output includes both `audit` and `onboard` commands\n    60ŌåÆ  - [x] 5.4: Target 100% coverage on the rewritten `onboard.ts`\n    61ŌåÆ\n    62ŌåÆ- [x] Task 6: Build and verify (AC: all)\n    63ŌåÆ  - [x] 6.1: Run `npm run build` ŌĆö verify tsup compiles successfully\n    64ŌåÆ  - [x] 6.2: Run `npm run test:unit` ŌĆö all tests pass, no regressions\n    65ŌåÆ  - [x] 6.3: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9) ŌĆö rewritten `onboard.ts` should be ~40-60 lines\n    66ŌåÆ  - [x] 6.4: Verify `codeharness onboard` runs end-to-end and produces audit output\n    67ŌåÆ  - [x] 6.5: Verify `codeharness audit` still works identically (no regression)\n    68ŌåÆ  - [x] 6.6: Verify `codeharness --help` shows both commands\n    69ŌåÆ\n    70ŌåÆ## Dev Notes\n    71ŌåÆ\n    72ŌåÆ### Architecture References\n    73ŌåÆ\n    74ŌåÆThis story implements FR16 (`onboard` becomes alias for `audit`). It replaces the old onboard command (which had its own scan/coverage/audit/epic pipeline) with a thin alias that delegates to the new audit coordinator from Story 3.1/3.2.\n    75ŌåÆ\n    76ŌåÆ### Key Implementation Details\n    77ŌåÆ\n    78ŌåÆ**Alias, not duplicate:** The onboard command must produce byte-identical output to audit. The cleanest approach is to extract the audit action handler into a shared function and call it from both commands. Do NOT copy-paste the audit logic into onboard.ts.\n    79ŌåÆ\n    80ŌåÆ**Legacy subcommand handling (AC #6):** The old `onboard` command had subcommands: `scan`, `coverage`, `audit`, `epic`. The new alias only needs to handle the bare `onboard` command (maps to `audit`) and provide a deprecation warning for `onboard scan`. The `coverage`, `audit`, and `epic` subcommands can be silently dropped ŌĆö they were internal to the old onboarding pipeline.\n    81ŌåÆ\n    82ŌåÆ**Shared state removal:** The old `onboard.ts` maintained module-level shared state (`lastScanResult`, `lastCoverageResult`, `lastAuditResult`) with getter/setter exports. These are no longer needed. Check if any other files import `getLastScanResult()`, `getLastCoverageResult()`, `getLastAuditResult()`, or `resetLastScanResult()` before removing ŌĆö the test file `onboard.test.ts` imports `resetLastScanResult` but that will be rewritten.\n    83ŌåÆ\n    84ŌåÆ**File size:** The rewritten `onboard.ts` should be dramatically smaller ŌĆö from 478 lines to ~40-60 lines. Well under NFR9's 300-line limit.\n    85ŌåÆ\n    86ŌåÆ### What NOT To Do\n    87ŌåÆ\n    88ŌåÆ- **Do NOT delete `src/lib/scanner.ts`, `src/lib/epic-generator.ts`, `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts`, `src/lib/scan-cache.ts`, `src/lib/beads-sync.ts`** ŌĆö other commands or tests may still use them. Only remove the imports from `onboard.ts`.\n    89ŌåÆ- **Do NOT modify `src/commands/audit.ts` behavior** ŌĆö the audit command must continue to work identically. Only refactor to extract a shared handler if needed.\n    90ŌåÆ- **Do NOT add new npm dependencies** ŌĆö this is pure refactoring.\n    91ŌåÆ- **Do NOT use `console.log` directly** ŌĆö use output utilities from `src/lib/output.ts`.\n    92ŌåÆ\n    93ŌåÆ### Existing Code to Reuse\n    94ŌåÆ\n    95ŌåÆ- `src/commands/audit.ts` ŌĆö `registerAuditCommand()`, the action handler logic to be shared\n    96ŌåÆ- `src/modules/audit/index.ts` ŌĆö `runAudit()`, `generateFixStories()`, `addFixStoriesToState()` barrel exports\n    97ŌåÆ- `src/modules/audit/report.ts` ŌĆö `formatAuditHuman()`, `formatAuditJson()` formatting\n    98ŌåÆ- `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` ŌĆö `runPreconditions()` (still needed for precondition check)\n    99ŌåÆ- `src/lib/output.ts` ŌĆö `ok()`, `fail()`, `info()`, `warn()`, `jsonOutput()` for output formatting\n   100ŌåÆ\n   101ŌåÆ### Dependencies\n   102ŌåÆ\n   103ŌåÆ- **Depends on:** Story 3.1 (audit coordinator ŌĆö `runAudit()`) ŌĆö DONE. Story 3.2 (audit --fix ŌĆö `generateFixStories()`) ŌĆö DONE.\n   104ŌåÆ- **Depended on by:** None within this epic.\n   105ŌåÆ\n   106ŌåÆ### File Size Constraint\n   107ŌåÆ\n   108ŌåÆEach new/modified file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n   109ŌåÆ- `src/commands/onboard.ts` ŌĆö ~40-60 lines (down from 478, alias only)\n   110ŌåÆ- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` ŌĆö ~80-100 lines (extracted shared handler, if created)\n   111ŌåÆ- `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` ŌĆö ~100-150 lines (simplified alias tests)\n   112ŌåÆ\n   113ŌåÆ### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 3.2)\n   114ŌåÆ\n   115ŌåÆ- **`runAudit()` returns `Promise<Result<AuditResult>>`** with `dimensions`, `overallStatus`, `gapCount`, `durationMs`.\n   116ŌåÆ- **`generateFixStories()` and `addFixStoriesToState()`** handle `--fix` logic.\n   117ŌåÆ- **`formatAuditHuman()` / `formatAuditJson()`** handle output formatting.\n   118ŌåÆ- **Commander.js** for CLI command registration with `.option()` and `.action()`.\n   119ŌåÆ- **`runPreconditions()`** from `src/lib/onboard-checks.js` for initialization check.\n   120ŌåÆ\n   121ŌåÆ### Git Intelligence\n   122ŌåÆ\n   123ŌåÆThe project uses Commander.js for CLI, vitest for testing, tsup for building. The existing `onboard.ts` is 478 lines with extensive functionality that is being replaced. The `audit.ts` command is 127 lines and well-structured.\n   124ŌåÆ\n   125ŌåÆ### References\n   126ŌåÆ\n   127ŌåÆ- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 3.3] ŌĆö Acceptance criteria\n   128ŌåÆ- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#FR16] ŌĆö `onboard` becomes alias for `audit`\n   129ŌåÆ- [Source: src/commands/audit.ts] ŌĆö Audit command to alias\n   130ŌåÆ- [Source: src/commands/onboard.ts] ŌĆö Existing onboard command to replace\n   131ŌåÆ- [Source: src/index.ts] ŌĆö Command registration\n   132ŌåÆ\n   133ŌåÆ### Project Structure Notes\n   134ŌåÆ\n   135ŌåÆ- Modified files: `src/commands/onboard.ts` (full rewrite as alias), `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` (full rewrite)\n   136ŌåÆ- Possibly new file: `src/commands/audit-action.ts` (shared handler extraction)\n   137ŌåÆ- Possibly modified: `src/commands/audit.ts` (if refactored to use shared handler)\n   138ŌåÆ- No patches created in this story\n   139ŌåÆ- Module follows existing conventions: Commander.js, Result<T> returns, <300 line files\n   140ŌåÆ\n   141ŌåÆ<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   142ŌåÆ## Verification Requirements\n   143ŌåÆ\n   144ŌåÆ- [x] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.proof.md`)\n   145ŌåÆ- [x] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   146ŌåÆ- [x] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   147ŌåÆ\n   148ŌåÆ## Documentation Requirements\n   149ŌåÆ\n   150ŌåÆ- [x] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/commands/AGENTS.md)\n   151ŌåÆ- [x] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.md`\n   152ŌåÆ\n   153ŌåÆ## Testing Requirements\n   154ŌåÆ\n   155ŌåÆ- [x] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   156ŌåÆ- [x] All I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n   157ŌåÆ- [x] Coverage target: 100%\n   158ŌåÆ<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   159ŌåÆ\n   160ŌåÆ## Dev Agent Record\n   161ŌåÆ\n   162ŌåÆ### Implementation Plan\n   163ŌåÆ\n   164ŌåÆ- Extract `executeAudit()` from `audit.ts` into shared `audit-action.ts` module\n   165ŌåÆ- Refactor `audit.ts` to be a thin wrapper calling `executeAudit()`\n   166ŌåÆ- Rewrite `onboard.ts` as a 40-line alias calling `executeAudit()`\n   167ŌåÆ- Add deprecated `scan` subcommand with warning\n   168ŌåÆ- Rewrite test file to verify alias delegation, deprecation warning, and help output\n   169ŌåÆ\n   170ŌåÆ### Completion Notes\n   171ŌåÆ\n   172ŌåÆ- Reduced `onboard.ts` from 478 lines to 40 lines (92% reduction)\n   173ŌåÆ- Created `audit-action.ts` (119 lines) as shared handler\n   174ŌåÆ- Simplified `audit.ts` from 127 lines to 25 lines\n   175ŌåÆ- All shared state exports (`getLastScanResult`, etc.) removed -- only used by onboard.ts and its tests\n   176ŌåÆ- All old imports removed from onboard.ts (scanner, epic-generator, beads, onboard-checks, scan-cache, beads-sync)\n   177ŌåÆ- Library files preserved -- only imports from onboard.ts were removed\n   178ŌåÆ- 100% statement/line/function coverage on onboard.ts and audit.ts\n   179ŌåÆ- 100% statement/line/function coverage on audit-action.ts (95.83% branch)\n   180ŌåÆ- Full test suite: 108 files, 2781 tests, 0 failures, 0 regressions\n   181ŌåÆ- Build: tsup compiles successfully\n   182ŌåÆ\n   183ŌåÆ## File List\n   184ŌåÆ\n   185ŌåÆ- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` (new) ŌĆö shared audit action handler\n   186ŌåÆ- `src/commands/audit.ts` (modified) ŌĆö thin wrapper using audit-action\n   187ŌåÆ- `src/commands/onboard.ts` (rewritten) ŌĆö thin alias for audit\n   188ŌåÆ- `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` (rewritten) ŌĆö alias behavior tests\n   189ŌåÆ- `src/commands/AGENTS.md` (updated) ŌĆö reflects new architecture\n   190ŌåÆ- `docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.md` (new) ŌĆö exec plan\n   191ŌåÆ- `docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.proof.md` (new) ŌĆö proof document\n   192ŌåÆ- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-onboard-alias.md` (updated) ŌĆö story file\n   193ŌåÆ\n   194ŌåÆ## Change Log\n   195ŌåÆ\n   196ŌåÆ- 2026-03-21: Implemented Story 3.3 ŌĆö replaced 478-line onboard command with 40-line alias delegating to shared audit handler. Extracted `executeAudit()` into `audit-action.ts`. Added deprecated `scan` subcommand. All 8 ACs satisfied. 108 test files, 2781 tests passing.\n   197ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d06dabce-ed3c-4abf-ad84-f2845532d39a","uuid":"98bafd73-6739-475c-affd-521827265bca","timestamp":"2026-03-21T05:07:48.248Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-3-3-onboard-alias/story.md","content":"# Story 3.3: Onboard Alias\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs an operator,\nI want `codeharness onboard` to work the same as `codeharness audit`,\nso that existing scripts and docs don't break when the audit command replaces onboard.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** `codeharness onboard` is run with no subcommand and no flags, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical output to `codeharness audit` (same dimension checks, same status/metric format, same exit code). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. **Given** `codeharness onboard --fix` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical output and behavior to `codeharness audit --fix` (generates fix stories for gaps, updates sprint state). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. **Given** `codeharness onboard --json` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical JSON output to `codeharness audit --json` (same structure, same fields). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. **Given** `codeharness onboard --fix --json` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it produces identical output to `codeharness audit --fix --json` (includes `fixStories` array in JSON). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. **Given** the harness is not initialized, **When** `codeharness onboard` is run, **Then** it exits with `[FAIL] Harness not initialized -- run codeharness init first` and exit code 1 ŌĆö same as `codeharness audit`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n6. **Given** `codeharness onboard scan` is run, **When** it executes, **Then** it prints a deprecation warning `[WARN] 'onboard scan' is deprecated ŌĆö use 'codeharness audit' instead` and then runs the audit command (maps legacy subcommand to new behavior). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n7. **Given** the old `registerOnboardCommand` function, **When** the alias is implemented, **Then** the old onboard command registration is removed from `src/index.ts` and replaced by the alias registration, so there is no duplicate command registration. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n8. **Given** `codeharness --help` is run, **When** the help output is displayed, **Then** both `audit` and `onboard` appear in the command list, with `onboard` described as `Alias for audit ŌĆö check all compliance dimensions`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Rewrite `src/commands/onboard.ts` as a thin alias (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7, #8)\n  - [x] 1.1: Remove all existing scan/coverage/audit/epic subcommand logic, shared state, and formatting helpers from `src/commands/onboard.ts`\n  - [x] 1.2: Implement `registerOnboardCommand(program)` that creates a `program.command('onboard')` with description `'Alias for audit ŌĆö check all compliance dimensions'`\n  - [x] 1.3: Mirror the `--json` and `--fix` options from the audit command\n  - [x] 1.4: In the action handler, delegate directly to the same logic as `registerAuditCommand` by calling the audit action internals (either extract shared handler or import and call `runAudit` / `generateFixStories` / `addFixStoriesToState` / formatting directly)\n  - [x] 1.5: Add deprecated `scan` subcommand that prints `[WARN] 'onboard scan' is deprecated ŌĆö use 'codeharness audit' instead` then runs audit logic (AC #6)\n\n- [x] Task 2: Extract shared audit action handler (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5)\n  - [x] 2.1: Extract the audit action logic from `src/commands/audit.ts` into a shared function `executeAudit(opts: { isJson: boolean; isFix: boolean }): Promise<void>` in a new file `src/commands/audit-action.ts` (or keep inline if both commands can import the same handler)\n  - [x] 2.2: Have both `registerAuditCommand` and `registerOnboardCommand` use the same handler, ensuring identical behavior\n  - [x] 2.3: Keep `registerAuditCommand` in `src/commands/audit.ts` unchanged (or with minimal refactor to use extracted handler)\n\n- [x] Task 3: Update `src/index.ts` registration (AC: #7)\n  - [x] 3.1: Verify `registerOnboardCommand(program)` is still called in `src/index.ts` ŌĆö the function name stays the same, only the implementation changes\n  - [x] 3.2: Verify no duplicate `audit` or `onboard` commands are registered\n\n- [x] Task 4: Remove dead code (AC: #7)\n  - [x] 4.1: Remove imports for `scanCodebase`, `analyzeCoverageGaps`, `auditDocumentation` from `src/lib/scanner.js` if no longer used elsewhere\n  - [x] 4.2: Remove imports for `generateOnboardingEpic`, `writeOnboardingEpic`, `formatEpicSummary`, `promptApproval`, `importOnboardingEpic` from `src/lib/epic-generator.js` if no longer used elsewhere\n  - [x] 4.3: Remove imports for `listIssues`, `createIssue` from `src/lib/beads.js` (onboard no longer calls beads directly)\n  - [x] 4.4: Remove imports for `filterTrackedGaps`, `findVerificationGaps`, `findPerFileCoverageGaps`, `findObservabilityGaps`, `getOnboardingProgress` from `src/lib/onboard-checks.js` if no longer used\n  - [x] 4.5: Remove imports for `saveScanCache`, `loadValidCache` from `src/lib/scan-cache.js` if no longer used\n  - [x] 4.6: Remove imports for `appendOnboardingEpicToSprint` from `src/lib/beads-sync.js` if no longer used\n  - [x] 4.7: Check all removed imports ŌĆö do NOT delete the library files themselves, only remove the imports from `onboard.ts`. Other commands may still use them.\n\n- [x] Task 5: Update tests (AC: all)\n  - [x] 5.1: Rewrite `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` to test the alias behavior:\n    - Test `codeharness onboard` delegates to audit logic\n    - Test `codeharness onboard --fix` delegates to audit --fix logic\n    - Test `codeharness onboard --json` produces same output as audit --json\n    - Test `codeharness onboard scan` prints deprecation warning and runs audit\n    - Test precondition failure (harness not initialized) produces same error as audit\n  - [x] 5.2: Mock the same dependencies as `audit.test.ts` (runPreconditions, runAudit, formatAuditHuman, formatAuditJson, generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState)\n  - [x] 5.3: Verify the `--help` output includes both `audit` and `onboard` commands\n  - [x] 5.4: Target 100% coverage on the rewritten `onboard.ts`\n\n- [x] Task 6: Build and verify (AC: all)\n  - [x] 6.1: Run `npm run build` ŌĆö verify tsup compiles successfully\n  - [x] 6.2: Run `npm run test:unit` ŌĆö all tests pass, no regressions\n  - [x] 6.3: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9) ŌĆö rewritten `onboard.ts` should be ~40-60 lines\n  - [x] 6.4: Verify `codeharness onboard` runs end-to-end and produces audit output\n  - [x] 6.5: Verify `codeharness audit` still works identically (no regression)\n  - [x] 6.6: Verify `codeharness --help` shows both commands\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture References\n\nThis story implements FR16 (`onboard` becomes alias for `audit`). It replaces the old onboard command (which had its own scan/coverage/audit/epic pipeline) with a thin alias that delegates to the new audit coordinator from Story 3.1/3.2.\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n**Alias, not duplicate:** The onboard command must produce byte-identical output to audit. The cleanest approach is to extract the audit action handler into a shared function and call it from both commands. Do NOT copy-paste the audit logic into onboard.ts.\n\n**Legacy subcommand handling (AC #6):** The old `onboard` command had subcommands: `scan`, `coverage`, `audit`, `epic`. The new alias only needs to handle the bare `onboard` command (maps to `audit`) and provide a deprecation warning for `onboard scan`. The `coverage`, `audit`, and `epic` subcommands can be silently dropped ŌĆö they were internal to the old onboarding pipeline.\n\n**Shared state removal:** The old `onboard.ts` maintained module-level shared state (`lastScanResult`, `lastCoverageResult`, `lastAuditResult`) with getter/setter exports. These are no longer needed. Check if any other files import `getLastScanResult()`, `getLastCoverageResult()`, `getLastAuditResult()`, or `resetLastScanResult()` before removing ŌĆö the test file `onboard.test.ts` imports `resetLastScanResult` but that will be rewritten.\n\n**File size:** The rewritten `onboard.ts` should be dramatically smaller ŌĆö from 478 lines to ~40-60 lines. Well under NFR9's 300-line limit.\n\n### What NOT To Do\n\n- **Do NOT delete `src/lib/scanner.ts`, `src/lib/epic-generator.ts`, `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts`, `src/lib/scan-cache.ts`, `src/lib/beads-sync.ts`** ŌĆö other commands or tests may still use them. Only remove the imports from `onboard.ts`.\n- **Do NOT modify `src/commands/audit.ts` behavior** ŌĆö the audit command must continue to work identically. Only refactor to extract a shared handler if needed.\n- **Do NOT add new npm dependencies** ŌĆö this is pure refactoring.\n- **Do NOT use `console.log` directly** ŌĆö use output utilities from `src/lib/output.ts`.\n\n### Existing Code to Reuse\n\n- `src/commands/audit.ts` ŌĆö `registerAuditCommand()`, the action handler logic to be shared\n- `src/modules/audit/index.ts` ŌĆö `runAudit()`, `generateFixStories()`, `addFixStoriesToState()` barrel exports\n- `src/modules/audit/report.ts` ŌĆö `formatAuditHuman()`, `formatAuditJson()` formatting\n- `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` ŌĆö `runPreconditions()` (still needed for precondition check)\n- `src/lib/output.ts` ŌĆö `ok()`, `fail()`, `info()`, `warn()`, `jsonOutput()` for output formatting\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- **Depends on:** Story 3.1 (audit coordinator ŌĆö `runAudit()`) ŌĆö DONE. Story 3.2 (audit --fix ŌĆö `generateFixStories()`) ŌĆö DONE.\n- **Depended on by:** None within this epic.\n\n### File Size Constraint\n\nEach new/modified file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n- `src/commands/onboard.ts` ŌĆö ~40-60 lines (down from 478, alias only)\n- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` ŌĆö ~80-100 lines (extracted shared handler, if created)\n- `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` ŌĆö ~100-150 lines (simplified alias tests)\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 3.2)\n\n- **`runAudit()` returns `Promise<Result<AuditResult>>`** with `dimensions`, `overallStatus`, `gapCount`, `durationMs`.\n- **`generateFixStories()` and `addFixStoriesToState()`** handle `--fix` logic.\n- **`formatAuditHuman()` / `formatAuditJson()`** handle output formatting.\n- **Commander.js** for CLI command registration with `.option()` and `.action()`.\n- **`runPreconditions()`** from `src/lib/onboard-checks.js` for initialization check.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nThe project uses Commander.js for CLI, vitest for testing, tsup for building. The existing `onboard.ts` is 478 lines with extensive functionality that is being replaced. The `audit.ts` command is 127 lines and well-structured.\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 3.3] ŌĆö Acceptance criteria\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#FR16] ŌĆö `onboard` becomes alias for `audit`\n- [Source: src/commands/audit.ts] ŌĆö Audit command to alias\n- [Source: src/commands/onboard.ts] ŌĆö Existing onboard command to replace\n- [Source: src/index.ts] ŌĆö Command registration\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- Modified files: `src/commands/onboard.ts` (full rewrite as alias), `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` (full rewrite)\n- Possibly new file: `src/commands/audit-action.ts` (shared handler extraction)\n- Possibly modified: `src/commands/audit.ts` (if refactored to use shared handler)\n- No patches created in this story\n- Module follows existing conventions: Commander.js, Result<T> returns, <300 line files\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [x] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.proof.md`)\n- [x] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [x] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [x] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/commands/AGENTS.md)\n- [x] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [x] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [x] All I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n- [x] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Implementation Plan\n\n- Extract `executeAudit()` from `audit.ts` into shared `audit-action.ts` module\n- Refactor `audit.ts` to be a thin wrapper calling `executeAudit()`\n- Rewrite `onboard.ts` as a 40-line alias calling `executeAudit()`\n- Add deprecated `scan` subcommand with warning\n- Rewrite test file to verify alias delegation, deprecation warning, and help output\n\n### Completion Notes\n\n- Reduced `onboard.ts` from 478 lines to 40 lines (92% reduction)\n- Created `audit-action.ts` (119 lines) as shared handler\n- Simplified `audit.ts` from 127 lines to 25 lines\n- All shared state exports (`getLastScanResult`, etc.) removed -- only used by onboard.ts and its tests\n- All old imports removed from onboard.ts (scanner, epic-generator, beads, onboard-checks, scan-cache, beads-sync)\n- Library files preserved -- only imports from onboard.ts were removed\n- 100% statement/line/function coverage on onboard.ts and audit.ts\n- 100% statement/line/function coverage on audit-action.ts (95.83% branch)\n- Full test suite: 108 files, 2781 tests, 0 failures, 0 regressions\n- Build: tsup compiles successfully\n\n## File List\n\n- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` (new) ŌĆö shared audit action handler\n- `src/commands/audit.ts` (modified) ŌĆö thin wrapper using audit-action\n- `src/commands/onboard.ts` (rewritten) ŌĆö thin alias for audit\n- `src/commands/__tests__/onboard.test.ts` (rewritten) ŌĆö alias behavior tests\n- `src/commands/AGENTS.md` (updated) ŌĆö reflects new architecture\n- `docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.md` (new) ŌĆö exec plan\n- `docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-onboard-alias.proof.md` (new) ŌĆö proof document\n- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-onboard-alias.md` (updated) ŌĆö story file\n\n## Change Log\n\n- 2026-03-21: Implemented Story 3.3 ŌĆö replaced 478-line onboard command with 40-line alias delegating to shared audit handler. Extracted `executeAudit()` into `audit-action.ts`. Added deprecated `scan` subcommand. All 8 ACs satisfied. 108 test files, 2781 tests passing.\n","numLines":197,"startLine":1,"totalLines":197}}}
